Bangkok Post
This is what a mob in Istanbul thought about Thailand's forced return of around 100 Uighur to China. The mob attacked the Thai honorary consul's office, causing extensive damage. (AP photo)
The government's expulsion of the group to China, after an earlier batch was sent to Turkey, has also drawn criticism by the UN and rights groups.

